f:\mathbb{R\cup\{-\infty,\infty\}}\to [0,1]
\lim_{b \to 0^+} f(\frac{a}{b})
\lim_{b \to 0^-} f(\frac{a}{b})
a \in \mathbb{R}^-
f(\lim_{b\to 0^+} \frac{a}{b})=f(-\infty)
f(\lim_{b\to 0^-} \frac{a}{b} )= f(\infty)
\mathbb{R}
\lim_{\alpha \rightarrow \beta^+} f(\alpha)= f(\beta), \qquad \beta\in\mathbb{R}\cup \{-\infty, + \infty\}.
i)
\frac{a}{b} \rightarrow -\infty
ii)
\frac{a}{b} \rightarrow +\infty
